title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer SIG50 (modified McMillan TAC-50) 50BMG with Muzzle Brake, Bipod & Leupold Mark 8 Scope
postcontent:
I am selling a brand new and never fired SIG Sauer® SIG50™ Bolt-Action Rifle. I bought it as an attempt to get back with my ex husband because our first date was at a shooting range but unfortunately, he is now muslim and does not believe in guns and being 9 months pregnant I really have no use for it. The gun is brand new in case. I put a scope on it, it’s the Leupold mark 8, 3.5-25x56mm illuminated Mil dot long range scope model number M5B2. This is the same exact setup that was used by tactical life magazine in testing this product, you can read more about their review here http://www.tactical-life.com/firearms/sig50-gun-test/#sig50-spread-2 and the video of them shooting it here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gm0tiFzwhJY Just that scope alone is $5K, the rifle itself IS in fact discontinued, I called Sig Sauer to find out why and it was because making it in Germany cost so much that they discontinued the product due to minimal profits from its production. It is indeed a very high quality product. The bolt feeds nice and cycles effortlessly. It is essentially a modified McMillon TAC 50 A1 with a sig P226 pistol grip for the handle, and while the TAC50 is still being made today, its retail price is over $12K, so asking $12.5K with scope and rings for a brand new one is reasonable, especially because of the fact that it is no longer being produced so the limited number out there will only assure that the value on this rifle will rise. Fun fact: the TAC50 holds the current record for world’s longest sniper killshot at 3871 Yards away, so if precision is what you’re after, this sub-MOA rifle is what you need. I will only show it to people with cash in hand because as I mentioned, I live alone and am very pregnant, so I need to see right away that you are serious about this rifle. With that being said, here is the manufacturer’s specifications sheet:
 
Bolt-action, five-round .50 BMG tactical rifle
Engineered with input from former military snipers
Recoil-mitigating recoil pad and muzzle brake
Removable stock for convenient transport
Match-grade, adjustable trigger can be set to 3.5 lbs.
Sig Sauer has produced quality firearms for military and law-enforcement personnel around the world. This tactical rifle chambared for the powerful .50 BMG cartridge is optimized for superior long-range performance. It was engineered based on input from former military snipers to ensure reliable performance in harsh conditions and repeatable accuracy. A bolt-action design with a five-round metal box magazine, it’s outfitted with a 29" barrel that features heavy fluting and six-groove 1:15 rifling with a right-hand twist. A side-ported, thread-on muzzle brake helps mitigate this potent gun’s recoil. The bolt is also fluted and equipped with a long bolt handle to ensure proper clearance for mounted optics. Sig50 includes a number of user-customizable features to enhance ergonomics. The cheek rest adjusts vertically, the buttplate is adjustable for length of pull and an ergonomic pistol grip aids shooter control and comfort. Machined M1913 rails allow for solid and repeatable mounting of optics, sighting aids and a bipod (a heavy-duty steel bipod is included). The single-stage adjustable trigger can be set to break cleanly as low as 3.5 lbs. Weather-resistant, anti-glare tan Duracoat coating adds protection from the elements. At just 23.5 lbs. empty, the Sig50 is comparatively light for a .50 BMG gun with magazine capability. The rifle’s overall length is 57". The stock can be removed to result in an overall length of 46.13" for enhanced portability.
